      <title>Salary vs Contract Rates</title>
      <link>http://www.snowfrog.net/2010/01/19/salary-vs-contract-rates/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 19 Jan 2010 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://www.snowfrog.net/2010/01/19/salary-vs-contract-rates/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve always wondered what recruitment agents use as their formula to convert between salaries and contract rates.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;(updated August 2015)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s a formula for giving ballpark figures, given to me by a
recruiter:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;Salary divided by 48 weeks, divided by 40 hours, plus 20% (super,
training, sick leave, etc) =~ Hourly rate
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, &lt;strong&gt;$100K =~ $62.50/hour&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;$150K =~ $93.75/hour&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

